-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 06:03AM EDT
-- None



Aug 8 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Friday:

** British engineering firm Hyder Consulting Plc <HYC.L> has accepted a 268 million pound ($451 million) takeover offer from Japan's Nippon Koei Co Ltd <1954.T>, just days after recommending a bid from Dutch firm Arcadis <ARDS.AS>. [ID:nL6N0QE1JD]  ** Malaysia's government will carry out a "complete overhaul" of its troubled national airline Malaysia Airline System <MASM.KL> in an attempt to revive the loss-making company after it was hit by two jetliner disasters this year. State investment fund Khazanah Nasional [KHAZA.UL] has proposed a 1.4 billion ringgit ($436 million) buy-out of the shares it does not own and take the airlines private. [ID:nL3N0OC176]  ** Gemalto NV <GTO.AS>, a digital security company that makes SIM cards for mobile phones and biometric passports, will buy U.S.-based data protection specialist SafeNet Inc [SFNT.UL] for $890 million in a move set to boost its earnings and reach. [ID:nL6N0QE14U]  ** Telecom Italia SpA <TLIT.MI> has lined up Citigroup <C.N>, Mediobanca <MDBI.MI> and Banco Bradesco SA <BBDC4.SA> to advise on a deal to acquire Vivendi's Brazilian unit GVT, people familiar with the situation said. [ID:nL6N0QD71H]  ** DirecTV <DTV.O> and AT&T Inc <T.N> would jointly own a Houston sports network under a plan to end the network's bankruptcy, although current part-owner Comcast Corp <CMCSA.O> warned it may challenge the proposal. [ID:nL2N0QD24F]  ** Australia's Clinuvel Pharmaceuticals Ltd <CUV.AX> rejected an unsolicited takeover proposal from biopharmaceutical company Retrophin Inc <RTRX.O>, saying the offer "materially undervalues the company". [ID:nL4N0QD7YD]  ** London-based private equity firm 3i Group Plc <III.L> had hired U.S. bank Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> to run a potential sale of British luxury lingerie retailer Agent Provocateur, the New York Times reported, citing a source. [ID:nL4N0QE04Q]  ** Singapore's competition watchdog has cleared a proposal from struggling budget airline Tiger Airways Ltd <TAHL.SI> and Scoot Pte Ltd to extend their partnership in a move that is expected to help both carriers boost traffic. [ID:nL4N0PB28A]  ** Turkish Islamic lender Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS> said an exclusive deal with Qatar Islamic Bank (QIB) <QISB.QA> to acquire a stake in the Turkish lender was annulled, opening the way for alternative suitors. [ID:nL6N0QE1Q3]